{"type":"text","timestamp":1781082969309,"sessionID":"ses_14f2faa5dffeNsrNVXSyL5rRxf","part":{"id":"prt_eb0d140ee00112U1ryDWGt5Rh4","messageID":"msg_eb0d137ba001MHoHslQzFdRo6J","sessionID":"ses_14f2faa5dffeNsrNVXSyL5rRxf","type":"text","text":"Now I have a full picture. Let me write the reward design report.\n\nSummary:\n- Single tier (`tier8_color_advanced`) is in scope, weighted 1.0\n- Scoring = (#tests passed in tier8) / (#tests total in tier8) — a simple pass-rate within the tier\n- Each test is a binary diff (oracle vs agent output, byte-exact match) → pass/fail per test\n- Failure paths emit reward 0 with `subscores=[]`\n- Atomic writes, schema-valid reward.json\n- Baseline (no rls implementation) → build fails → reward 0\n- Trivial outputs (empty, hello world) → all diffs fail → 0\n- Tests cover many sub-dimensions inside tier8: color (always/never/long), ignore/hide filtering, SELinux context (-Z), and multi-flag combos/overrides","time":{"start":1781082964206,"end":1781082969270}}}
