{"type":"text","timestamp":1781083001975,"sessionID":"ses_14f2faa5dffeNsrNVXSyL5rRxf","part":{"id":"prt_eb0d1c0c2001PofVi2HK1oytgp","messageID":"msg_eb0d1b107001sFYit5jTzDaNyj","sessionID":"ses_14f2faa5dffeNsrNVXSyL5rRxf","type":"text","text":"Reward design report written. Summary:\n\n**Status: PASS**\n\nThe reward formula is a weighted pass-rate where only `tier8_color_advanced` is in scope (weight 1.0), so `score = tier8_pass / tier8_total`. Each test is a binary byte-exact diff against the trusted GNU `ls` oracle output.\n\nKey findings:\n- **Correctness gating**: Bad/empty outputs fail byte-exact diff and score 0\n- **Implementation-agnostic**: Only measures output equivalence, no implementation specifics\n- **Dimension balance**: Sub-dimensions (color, ignore/hide, -Z, flag combos) are flattened as equally-weighted binary cases within one tier — no single dimension can be gamed while ignoring others\n- **Shortcut-resistant**: Build-from-source enforced, oracle hash check, banned-crate greps, strace tripwires\n- **Modular scoring**: `compute_reward.py` runs outside strace, reads only a subscores file, never imports agent code\n- **Schema**: Atomic writes via tmpfile+`os.replace`; failure paths emit `subscores=[]`","time":{"start":1781082996930,"end":1781083001973}}}
